# Frontend Environment Configuration

The frontend automatically detects development vs production mode and uses appropriate URLs.

## Automatic Environment Detection

The app uses Flutter's `kDebugMode` to determine the environment:

### Development Mode (Debug builds)
- API Base URL: `http://localhost:3000/api` (web/iOS)
- API Base URL: `http://10.0.2.2:3000/api` (Android emulator)
- Storage Base URL: `http://localhost:3000/storage`

### Production Mode (Release builds)
- API Base URL: `https://admin.namkeentv.com/api`
- Storage Base URL: `https://storage.googleapis.com/namkeen-tv`

## Running in Development

Just run `flutter run` and it will automatically use localhost:

```bash
# Web
flutter run -d chrome

# Mobile
flutter run -d <device-id>
```

See [DEV_SETUP.md](DEV_SETUP.md) for detailed instructions.

## Override URLs (Optional)

Use `--dart-define` to override URLs:

```bash
flutter run --dart-define=API_BASE_URL=https://staging.example.com/api
```

## Docker Deployment (Production)

Set these environment variables:

```bash
API_BASE_URL=https://admin.namkeentv.com/api
STORAGE_BASE_URL=https://storage.googleapis.com/namkeen-tv
```

These are injected at runtime via `docker-entrypoint.sh`.
